### API Testing Guide
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080

### ============================================
### 1. PUBLIC ENDPOINTS (No Auth Required)
### ============================================

### GET /welcome
GET http://localhost:8080/welcome

### GET /send-email
GET http://localhost:8080/send-email

### ============================================
### 2. AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
### ============================================

### POST /signup - Create new user
POST http://localhost:8080/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### POST /login - Get JWT token
POST http://localhost:8080/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ============================================
### 3. JWT-PROTECTED ENDPOINTS (Bearer token)
### ============================================

### GET /me - Protected route
### Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with token from /login
GET http://localhost:8080/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### GET /admin - Admin only route
### Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE with admin token
GET http://localhost:8080/admin
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### TESTING WORKFLOW
### ============================================
### 1. Run: POST /signup (create user)
### 2. Run: POST /login (get token)
### 3. Copy token from response
### 4. Replace YOUR_TOKEN_HERE in protected routes
### 5. Test protected endpoints
